The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques for solving the textbook question answering (TQA) task. The use of knowledge graph and graph convolutional network (GCN) suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of NLP and ML related to knowledge representation and reasoning, such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of unsupervised learning for text comprehension suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of NLP and ML related to text mining and information retrieval, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of deep learning techniques such as GCN suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of deep learning, such as cs.DL (Machine Learning).
